We start by extracting the key figures from the provided financial data.

Step 1. Gross Profit Margin
• From the income statement, we have:
 – Gross Profit = 5,718,450.67 
 – Total Revenue = 20,318,450.67  
• The formula for Gross Profit Margin is:
  Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• Calculation:
  = (5,718,450.67 / 20,318,450.67) × 100%
  ≈ 0.2814 × 100%
  ≈ 28.14%

Step 2. Operating Cash Flow Ratio
• From the cash flow statement, the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities is given as –18,924,462.44.
• From the balance sheet, the Total Current Liabilities are 1,015,922.54.
• The Operating Cash Flow Ratio is computed as:
  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)
• Calculation:
  = –18,924,462.44 / 1,015,922.54
  ≈ –18.63

Thus, we have:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "28.14%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-18.63"
  }
}
